explanation: This solution uses a two-pointer approach. First, it sorts the string and then iterates over the sorted string. For each character, it checks if it has been visited before. If not, it adds the character to the result and marks it as visited. Then, it removes characters from the end of the result that are greater than the current character until it finds a character that has not been visited before. This ensures that the result is lexicographically smallest.

